# Example Commit Message Templates for gh-commit-ai
#
# Copy this file to .gh-commit-ai-template in your repo root to customize
# your commit message format.
#
# Available template variables:
#   {{emoji}}          - Gitmoji emoji (if USE_GITMOJI=true)
#   {{type}}           - Commit type (feat, fix, docs, etc.)
#   {{scope}}          - Scope with parentheses (auth), or empty
#   {{breaking_marker}} - ! if breaking change, empty otherwise
#   {{message}}        - Summary message
#   {{bullets}}        - Bullet points with changes
#   {{breaking}}       - BREAKING CHANGE footer if present
#   {{ticket}}         - Ticket number from branch (e.g., ABC-123)
#   {{branch}}         - Current branch name
#   {{author}}         - Git author name
#   {{date}}           - Current date (YYYY-MM-DD)
#   {{files_changed}}  - Number of files changed
#
# Note: Empty variables are automatically removed from the output.

# ============================================================================
# DEFAULT TEMPLATE (same as built-in format)
# ============================================================================
# This is the standard conventional commit format used by gh-commit-ai:

{{emoji}} {{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}

{{bullets}}
{{breaking}}


# ============================================================================
# TEMPLATE WITH TICKET NUMBER
# ============================================================================
# Automatically includes ticket number from branch name:

{{emoji}} {{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}

{{bullets}}
{{breaking}}

Ticket: {{ticket}}


# ============================================================================
# DETAILED TEMPLATE WITH METADATA
# ============================================================================
# Includes additional context about the commit:

{{emoji}} {{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}

{{bullets}}
{{breaking}}

Branch: {{branch}}
Ticket: {{ticket}}
Files: {{files_changed}} changed
Date: {{date}}


# ============================================================================
# ANGULAR STYLE TEMPLATE
# ============================================================================
# Follows Angular commit message conventions:

{{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}

{{bullets}}

{{breaking}}


# ============================================================================
# MINIMAL TEMPLATE (no bullets)
# ============================================================================
# Just the summary line:

{{emoji}} {{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}


# ============================================================================
# CUSTOM PROJECT TEMPLATE
# ============================================================================
# Example for projects with specific requirements:

[{{ticket}}] {{emoji}} {{type}}{{scope}}: {{message}}

Changes:
{{bullets}}

{{breaking}}

Reviewed-by: {{author}}
Committed: {{date}}


# ============================================================================
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Choose one of the templates above (or create your own)
# 2. Copy it to .gh-commit-ai-template in your repo root
# 3. Remove all the comments and example templates
# 4. The AI will automatically format messages using your template
#
# Example minimal setup:
#   $ cp .gh-commit-ai-template.example .gh-commit-ai-template
#   $ edit .gh-commit-ai-template  # Keep only the template you want
#   $ gh commit-ai                 # Will use your custom template
#
# Tips:
# - Variables that are empty will be removed automatically
# - Blank lines in the template are preserved
# - The AI generates the content; template just formats it
# - You can mix and match variables however you like
#
